x>\\frac{1}{2}(cos(A+B) + cos(A-B)) = cos Acos B </latex>',1,2,0,1),(192,2185,'Det','In the given question, three cosines of frequencies f, 2f and 3f are multiplied with each other.\r\nMultiplying the first and second cosines with each other, we get a sum of two cosines with frequencies 3f and f. Multiplying this sum with the cosine of frequency 3f, we get a sum of four cosines with frequencies 9f, 3f, 5f, and 7f. Therefore, since not all these frequencies obey the condition f < 2fs, the signal aliases. ',0,0,0,1),(193,2185,'Sol','A',0,0,0,1),(194,2228,'Hint','<latex> x(t) * \\ delta(t-a) = x(a) * \\ delta(t-a) </latex>',0,0,0,1),(195,2228,'Sol','C',0,0,0,1),(196,2228,'Det','<latex> x(t) * \\ delta(t-a) = x(a) * \\ delta(t-a) </latex> <br><br>\r\n<latex> y(t) =  x(t) * [\\delta(t-1)-\\delta(t-4)] </latex><br><br>\r\nTherefore, \r\n<br> <latex> y(t) =  (x(1) *\\delta(t-1))- (x(4) *\\delta(t-4))</latex><br><br>\r\n\r\nFrom the diagram,<br><br>\r\nx(1) = 1 <br>\r\nx(4) = 0<br><br>\r\n\r\nTherefore <br>\r\n<latex> y(t) =  (1 *\\delta(t-1))</latex>',0,0,0,1),(197,2186,'Hint','In a signal which is the sum of three frequencies, if any of the frequencies disobeys the condition f < 2fs, the signal aliases.',0,0,0,1),(198,2186,'Sol','A',0,0,0,1),(199,574,'Hint','<latex>f_i(t) =\\frac{1}{2*pi}\\frac{d}{dt}psi(t) </latex>',0,0,0,1),(200,574,'Sol','d-2eb',0,0,0,1),(201,2186,'Det','f, 2f and 3f are all less than fs/2. Therefore, the signal does not alias.',0,0,0,1),(202,574,'Det','<latex>f_i(t) =\\frac{1}{2*pi}\\frac{d}{dt}psi(t) </latex>\r\n\r\n<latex> f_i(t) = d - 2*e*t </latex><br><br>\r\nThis is a decreasing frequency. Hence min occurs at t = b<br>\r\n\r\n<latex> f_i(b) = Min f_i = d - 2*e*b</latex>',0,0,0,1),(203,3315,'Hint','<latex>omega_{hat} =\\frac{2*pi*f}{f_s}+ 2*pi*l</latex>\r\n',0,0,0,1),(205,3315,'Sol','B',0,0,0,1),(206,557,'Hint','Time period = (1/f_min)',0,0,0,1),(207,557,'Sol','Time period = (1/2*479)',0,0,0,1),(208,557,'Det','Highest Frequency = 2*<latex>\\pi</la